description._content: Description: A typical native Court House in the Gilberts. Here the "bowl", or island Native Government meet to administer the law and discuss the affairs of the island. Location: Gilberts, Kiribati ------------------------------------------------------ Description: A Gilbert island Native Government station. Re-thatching the houses of the Native Magistrate and other island officials. Location: Gilbert Island, Kiribati ------------------------------------------------------ Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/642. This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons. Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown.
